                <h1>Understanding Padded Rooms: Safety & Design</h1>
                <p>A padded room is designed to provide a safe environment for individuals who may pose a risk to themselves or others. Commonly found in psychiatric facilities, these rooms feature walls and surfaces cushioned with soft materials to minimize injury during episodes of agitation or stress, promoting calm and safety.</p>
